🧪 Lab 03 – Spanning Tree Protocol (STP) Root Manipulation & Port Protection
📌 Overview
This lab demonstrates IEEE 802.1D Spanning Tree Protocol (STP) behavior in a multi-switch topology with redundant links.
The objectives were to:
Identify the default root bridge
Analyze STP port roles and states
Manually manipulate root bridge election per VLAN
Influence path selection using cost and port priority
Configure PortFast and BPDU Guard
Observe STP convergence and err-disable behavior
Platform: Cisco Catalyst 2960 (Packet Tracer)
Protocol: IEEE 802.1D STP
VLANs Used: VLAN 1 and VLAN 2
🗺 Topology






4
Four switches were connected with redundant Layer 2 links to intentionally create potential switching loops.
